docs.abstract: The 10-day, 1,600-mile race in the desert, starting next week, challenges body and mind and helps competitors find themselves.
docs.snippet: The 10-day, 1,600-mile race in the desert, starting next week, challenges body and mind and helps competitors find themselves.
docs.lead_paragraph: Over 10 days, they will drive across 1,600 grueling, off-road miles in the Nevada and California deserts, where the afternoons can reach 100 degrees and the nights can dip to 15. On their hunt for just under 200 hidden checkpoints, they will rely on map and compass skills, as well as driving prowess, physical stamina and more.

headline.main: Only the ‘Most Hard-Core Women’ Go Off-Road for Rebelle Rally
headline.print_headline: For Women Only: An ‘Insane Obstacle Course’
